'''Ángelo Smit Preciado Quiñónez''' (born 18 February 1998) is an Ecuadorian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right-back]] or [[winger (association football)|winger]] for [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] club [[Clube Atlético Mineiro|Atlético Mineiro]] and the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador national team]].<ref name="SW"/>

==Club career==
Born in [[Shushufindi Canton|Shushufindi]], [[Sucumbíos Province|Sucumbíos]], Preciado joined [[C.S.D. Independiente del Valle|Independiente del Valle]]'s youth setup in 2015, from [[América de Quito]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eltelegrafo.com.ec/noticias/futbol/1/preciado-le-dedicara-el-mundial-a-su-padre|title=Preciado le dedicará el mundial a su padre|trans-title=Preciado will dedicate the World Cup to his father|publisher=[[El Telégrafo (Ecuador)|El Telégrafo]]|language=es|date=16 May 2017|accessdate=4 December 2019}}</ref> In February 2018, during the semifinals of the [[2018 U-20 Copa Libertadores]], he went viral after using the [[corner flag]] to defend himself from a fight with the [[Club Atlético River Plate (Montevideo)|River Plate Montevideo]] players.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.benditofutbol.com/independiente-del-valle/angelo-preciado-copalibertadores-sub20-banderin.html|title=¿Quién es el futbolista que se defendió con el banderín en la Libertadores Sub 20?|trans-title=Who is the footballer who defended himself with the corner flag in the U-20 Libertadores?|publisher=Bendito Fútbol|language=es|date=22 February 2018|accessdate=4 December 2019}}</ref>

Promoted to the first team after playing a short period in the [[reserve team]], [[Alianza Cotopaxi S.C.|Alianza Cotopaxi]], Preciado made his senior – and [[Ecuadorian Serie A|Serie A]] – debut on 9 July 2018, starting in a 3–1 away loss against [[S.D. Aucas|Aucas]]. He soon became a regular starter, and scored his first goals on 25 August by netting a brace in a 4–2 home defeat of [[C.D. El Nacional|El Nacional]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elcomercio.com/deportes/independientedelvalle-elnacional-estadioruminahui-campeonatoecuatoriano-segundaetapa.html|title=Independiente remontó y ganó 4–2 a El Nacional en Sangolquí|trans-title=Independiente completed a comeback and defeated El Nacional by 4–2 in Sangolquí|publisher=[[El Comercio (Ecuador)|El Comercio]]|language=es|date=25 August 2018|accessdate=4 December 2019}}</ref>

On 28 December 2020, [[Belgian Pro League]] club [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]] announced the signing of Preciado on a two-and-a-half-year contract, with an option for a further two years,<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=28 December 2020 |title=Ecuadoraanse international Angelo Preciado is op komst! |trans-title=Ecuadorian international Angelo Preciado is on his way! |url=https://www.krcgenk.be/nl/nieuws/4108/ecuadoraanse-international-angelo-preciado-is-op-komst |access-date=2023-09-04 |website=krcgenk.be |publisher=KRC Genk |language=nl}}</ref> for a reported fee of €3 million.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-01-04 |title=Genk sign 18 year old Ecuadorian defender Alfred Caicedo |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/genk-sign-18-year-old-ecuadorian-defender-alfred-caicedo-36528192 |access-date=2023-09-04 |website=OneFootball}}</ref> He made his debut for the Belgian club on 16 January 2021, starting in a 2–0 away loss at [[Royal Excel Mouscron]].<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=16 January 2021 |title=Met 2-0 onderuit op sneeuwtapijt |trans-title=Down 2-0 on snow carpet |url=https://www.krcgenk.be/nl/nieuws/4125/met-2-0-onderuit-op-sneeuwtapijt |access-date=2023-09-04 |website=krcgenk.be |publisher=KRC Genk |language=nl}}</ref>

On 4 September 2023, [[Czech First League]] club [[AC Sparta Prague|Sparta Prague]] announced the signing of Preciado for a reported fee of €2.5 million, which could increase to €3 million with add-ons.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=2023-09-04 |title=Angelo Preciado troca o Genk pelo Sparta Praga |trans-title=Angelo Preciado trades Genk for Sparta Prague |url=https://bolanarede.pt/especial-bola-na-rede/ultima-hora/angelo-preciado-troca-o-genk-pelo-sparta-praga/ |access-date= |website=Bola na Rede |language=pt}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=4 September 2023 |title=New Spartan: Angelo Preciado |url=https://sparta.cz/en/article/new-spartan-angelo-preciado-41478 |access-date=4 September 2023 |website=[[AC Sparta Prague]]}}</ref> On 15 February 2024, he scored his first goal in the [[2023–24 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]] in a 3–2 defeat to [[Galatasaray S.K.|Galatasaray]].<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/691526/sparta-prague-galatasaray|website=ESPN|date=15 February 2024|accessdate=7 March 2024|title= 2023-24 UEFA Europa League, Knockout Round Playoffs}}</ref>

On 16 January 2026, Preciado joined [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] club [[Clube Atlético Mineiro|Atlético Mineiro]] on a four-year contract.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Preciado é do Galo! |trans-title=Preciado to Galo! |url=https://atletico.com.br/comunicado-do-galo-angelo-preciado/ |date=16 January 2026 |access-date=17 January 2026 |publisher=Clube Atlético Mineiro |language=pt}}</ref>

==International career==
On 4 May 2017, Preciado was called up to [[Ecuador national under-20 football team|Ecuador under-20s]] for [[2017 FIFA U-20 World Cup|the year]]'s [[FIFA U-20 World Cup]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.andes.info.ec/es/noticias/ecuador-elige-juveniles-participaran-mundial-sub-20-corea-sur-2017.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170505014521/http://www.andes.info.ec/es/noticias/ecuador-elige-juveniles-participaran-mundial-sub-20-corea-sur-2017.html|title=Ecuador elige a los juveniles que participarán en el Mundial Sub 20 Corea del Sur 2017|trans-title=Ecuador choose the youngsters who will take part of U-20 World Cup South Korea 2017|publisher=[[Public News Agency of Ecuador and South America|ANDES]]|language=es|date=4 May 2017|archive-date=5 May 2017|access-date=4 December 2019}}</ref> On 30 August of the following year, he was called up to [[Ecuador national football team|the full side]] by manager [[Hernán Darío Gómez]], for two [[Exhibition match|friendlies]] against [[Jamaica national football team|Jamaica]] and [[Guatemala national football team|Guatemala]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eluniverso.com/deportes/2018/08/30/nota/6930152/22-convocados-hernan-dario-gomez-partidos-amistosos-ante-jamaica|title=Los 22 convocados de Hernán Darío Gómez para los partidos amistosos ante Jamaica y Guatemala|trans-title=The 22 called up by Hernán Darío Gómez for the friendly matches against Jamaica and Guatemala|publisher=[[El Universo]]|language=es|date=30 August 2019|access-date=4 December 2019}}</ref>

Preciado made his full international debut on 12 October 2018, replacing Independiente teammate [[Stiven Plaza]] in a 4–3 loss against [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]] at the [[Jassim bin Hamad Stadium]] in [[Doha]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elcomercio.com/deportes/ecuador-experiencia-juventud-catar-amistoso.html|title=Goles y errores en la derrota 4–3 de Ecuador ante Catar en Doha|trans-title=Goals and errors in Ecuador's 4–3 defeat to Qatar in Doha|publisher=El Comercio|language=es|date=12 October 2018|access-date=4 December 2019}}</ref>

Preciado was selected in the 28 player Ecuador squad for the [[2021 Copa América]].<ref>{{cite tweet|author=[[Ecuadorian Football Federation]]|user=LaTri|number=1402825519754797058|title=¡Y los convocados son! Estos son los elegidos por el DT #GustavoAlfaro para encarar un desafío continental: la @CopaAmerica.|date=9 June 2021|access-date=9 June 2021|language=es}}</ref>

Preciado was named in the Ecuadorian squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite tweet |author=Ecuador national football team |author-link=Ecuador national football team |user=LaTri |number=1592288685797494784 |date=14 November 2022 |title=Aquí están los 26 jugadores elegidos por el DT Gustavo Alfaro para jugar la Copa Mundial FIFA, estamos listos para hacer historia |trans-title=Here are the 26 players chosen by head coach Gustavo Alfaro to play the FIFA World Cup, we are ready to make history. |language=es |access-date=14 November 2022}}</ref>

Preciado was called up to the final 26-man Ecuador squad for the [[2024 Copa América]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eluniverso.com/deportes/futbol/ecuador-presenta-lista-oficial-para-la-copa-america-gonzalo-plata-y-robert-arboleda-quedaron-relegados-nota/|title=Ecuador presenta lista oficial para la Copa América: Gonzalo Plata y Robert Arboleda quedaron relegados|trans-title=Ecuador presents official roster for Copa America: Gonzalo Plata and Robert Arboleda left off the list|publisher=[[El Universo]]|date=29 May 2024|language=es}}</ref>

